Unfortunately TypeScript sees no difference between these two examples:

```ts
render={(props) => <Component {...props} />}
```

```ts
render={(props) => {
  useSomeHook();
  return <Component {...props} />}
}
```

Most of the time the second example would work just fine, so you'd have no idea you did anything wrong—until it started to crash in some specific scenario much later, which is what happened to us.

I'll see if I can find a short-term solution for our codebase, e.g. a `no-restricted-syntax` rule in ESLint, to make sure we don't make this mistake again.

```jsx
