@spacecat Did you read the other comments from atomiks? The `isolation: isolate` attribute is required for any components that require a portal. This includes, at least: Alert Dialog; Context Menu; Dialog; Menu; Menubar; Navigation Menu; Popover; Preview Card; Select; Toast; Tooltip; and the upcoming Combobox. If this step wasn't included by default, then I'd bet a couple bucks that many Github issues would be opened asking "Why doesn't Select work?".

I've used other UI libraries and this is the first one I've had to do this `isolation` CSS change. However, it has made working with the library's components much easier than others, e.g. Radix or MUI. I don't have to muck about with the z-index value for anything. This is a better DX than having to fight with z-index bugs.

This is by far and large not "bad DX", truly not even close.

